<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Cloudburst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-27 11:04:16</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>With regard to the above post about 2 yaks and FBSS for the Kedge, the answer is absolutely yes, at least on Veeshan.<BR>
<BR>
On Veeshan, you could get easily get more if you're patient.  As an example, the reed belts now are priced right around Golden Eff. Boots range, which is 15-18 K pp on Veeshan.  You can also get 2 yaks or dang close with reed belt.  Yaks are pretty common now in Freeport for 7 K pp, and the asking price on FBSS are 15 K pp.  Given that the Kedge Totem is the rare drop, there is no doubt in my mind that you could hold out for quite a bit more than the 2 yaks and FBSS.  Again, this is on Veeshan, no idea what the economy is like on other servers.<BR>
<BR>
Oh, and as for those who say, he spawns right at this precise location <enter one of a dozen spots in DC>, the answer is nope.  I mean the guy wanders like a madman and there is no way (in my opinion) he spawns at one point.  Even if he ends up at a particular point in DC (i.e., he has ONE placeholder who follows a particular path which I think unlikely), I don't think it's a great strategy to sit at the loc, turn on the TV, and hope he'll pass through.  More likely one of several trackers on at the same time will kill him long before he reaches your spot.  And then you log after eight hours and think, man, Bilge didn't spawn all day.  And you'd be wrong.<BR>
<BR>
My advice - kill tons of gobs and keep tracking in different areas of zone.<BR>
<BR>
Cloudburst</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
